<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="379" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="379">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="379">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Flatidae" genus="Flata" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flata splendens" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">Flata splendens</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Germar, EF" journalOrPublisher="Thon's Entomologisches Archiv" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" pagination="1 - 57" title="Species Cicadarium enumeratae et sub genera distributae." volume="2" year="1830">Germar (1830)</bibRefCitation>
from Java, and was designated as the type species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Anagnia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anagnia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anagnia</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C" journalOrPublisher="Herausgegeben von dem entomologischen Vereine zu Stettin" pageId="13" pageNumber="382" pagination="129 - 153" title="Miscellanea hemopterologica. Entomologische Zeitung." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12401" volume="22" year="1861">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stål">Stal</normalizedToken>
(1861)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar, 1903" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Udugama" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Udugama flavocarinata" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavocarinata">Udugama flavocarinata</taxonomicName>
Bierman, 1907 from Java was considered as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. splendens" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" rank="species" species="splendens">O. splendens</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Melichar, L" journalOrPublisher="Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" pagination="1 - 221" title="Monographie der Dictyophorinen (Homoptera). Abhandlungen der K. K." volume="7" year="1912">Melichar (1912)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus splendens var. tibialis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="splendens" variety="tibialis">Orthopagus splendens var. tibialis</taxonomicName>
Kirkaldy was differentiated from the typical form by having &quot;the fore and middle tibiae distinctly bi- or tri-angulate with brownish&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy, GW" journalOrPublisher="Report of the work of the Experiment Station of the Hawaiian Sugar Plantersʼ Association, Entomological series, Bulletin Honolulu" pageId="12" pageNumber="381" pagination="1 - 90" title="On some new species of leaf-hoppers." volume="12" year="1913">Kirkaldy and Muir 1913</bibRefCitation>
). However, this pattern is typical for all 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Orthopagus</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="379">
The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Dictyophara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dictyophara indiana" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indiana">Dictyophara indiana</taxonomicName>
Walker, 1851 with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus splendens" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">Orthopagus splendens</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C" journalOrPublisher="Herausgegeben von dem entomologischen Vereine zu Stettin" pageId="13" pageNumber="382" pagination="129 - 153" title="Miscellanea hemopterologica. Entomologische Zeitung." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12401" volume="22" year="1861">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stål">Stal</normalizedToken>
(1861)
</bibRefCitation>
is considered doubtful (see above).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="379">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dictyopharidae" genus="Orthopagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthopagus splendens" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens">Orthopagus splendens</taxonomicName>
has been frequently confused in literature and museum collections with other species of the genus. It can be differentiated from them by the combination of the following characters: a relatively small body size, a moderately short head, an extensive dark pattern on vertex, the pygofer with dorso-posterior margin bearing a relatively large but narrow, simply tooth-like process, the endosomal processes of the aedeagus relatively long and robust, covered with minute superficial spines and phallotheca bearing two pairs of membranous lobes.
</paragraph>
